This directory is where we will develop the on-line system that colors
edits according to trust in real-time, as they are made. 

To have the code work, you need: 

- Install mysql and mediawiki

- Install the following packages: 
    ocaml-findlib
    libmysql-ocaml
    libmysql-ocaml-dev
    libextlib-ocaml-dev
    python-mysqldb

- Make OcamlLdaLibs and install them (see instructions there). 

- Make batch/analysis (see instructions there); installation is not
  necessary. 

- Make online/analysis (see instructions there); installation is not
  necessary. 

- Populate the mysql db with some test data.  To do so:

  $ cd online/wikifeed
  $ cp db_access_data.ini.sample db_access_data.ini
  $ nano db_access_data.ini

  and fill db_access_data.ini with the data to access your database: 
  host: you can use "localhost"
  user: this is the wiki user name.  Usually, this is "wikiuser". 
  pass: this is the password that you gave for mysql when installing
  mediawiki. 
  db: the mediawiki db, usually "wikidb". 

  Then, go to the test-data directory, and fill the database with
  data.  Precisely: 

  $ cd ../test-data
  $ cp script.sh.template script.sh
  $ nano script.sh 

  and insert the mysql root password where required. 
  Optionally, comment out the last "ocamldebug" line if you wish; you
  can always execute eval_online_wiki separately. 
  Then, execute the script: 

  $ ./script.sh

- From here on, all you need to do is run
  online/analysis/eval_online_wiki, and this will color the wiki
  revisions in the database: 

  $ ./eval_online_wiki -db_user wikiuser -db_pass <pwd> -db_name wikidb -log_name ~/temp/color.log

- If the database tables to be used for the coloring ever change,
  remove the old ones with sql/remove_wikitrust_tables.sql, as in: 

  $ cd ../sql
  $ mysql -u root -p wikidb
  mysql> \. remove_wikitrust_tables.sql
  mysql> \. create_wikitrust_tables.sql
 
================================================================


  
